    ],
    "summary": "On 9-May-2018 at approximately 10:30 hours, a fire occurred in the temporary quarters of Platform EB 165 A. A mechanic discovered charred soot on the temporary quarters entrance door while conducting holding checks on SSVs during compressor maintenance shutdown. The alarm was sounded, muster was initiated, and personnel investigated. No visible flame was detected. Fire investigation determined the fire started on a lower bunk mattress, with the probable cause being a cracked reading light bulb, though the cause was ultimately determined to be undetermined and accidental in origin. The fire self-extinguished due to lack of oxygen. Estimated damage was $75,000.",
